node.text:
I recently started following this bomb.com self help coach on my personal Instagram account. @therealjoirizarry 

Her daily convos/advice/ viewpoints are spot on in this stage of growth and healing. 

This particular post resonates with me as I started setting hella boundaries. Now I can identify that empty feeling, the loss that she speaks of. Maybe you can relate?

node.text:
I recently started following this bomb.com self help coach on my personal Instagram account. @therealjoirizarry 

Her daily convos/advice/ viewpoints are spot on in this stage of growth and healing. 

This particular post resonates with me as I started setting hella boundaries. Now I can identify that empty feeling, the loss that she speaks of. Maybe you can relate?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'GODFATHER GOTTI! @Gotti2Hottiee same Y'all get irritated with people fast because y'all parents did the with you. Y'all can't communicate because y'all parents couldn't. Y'all think yelling /being aggressive every time u disagree with something is okay because y'all parents yelled/ got hostile when they...'.

node.text:
Not just your parents, but any damaged relationship you still carry with you today. 

As we carry on the generational curse of dysfunction we also teach people how it’s ok to speak to and treat us. We’re giving them our language. 

We don’t have to carry this behavior on. We can say no and treat others how we want to be treated instead of how we are treated. 

Let’s break the cycle. - @therealjoirizarry 

@gottie2hottiee on Twitter

node.text:
It’s not just the “hurt”that causes you pain.

I  need to feel the betrayal, the heartache, the sadness, the loneliness, the neglect. I need to process all these things.  Give those feelings big girl words. 

Feel it, that thing that you don’t want to, feel it and be free. 

This message is for you and this message is for me. - @therealjoirizarry

Please don’t do this to people when they reach out. Be kind, be understanding and please try to listen. - @tanner_hamilton22
